The course is a training of oral and written expression on the independent user's level (B1-B2), to assure an equal level for new students in the French Department. The training of oral speech involves various topics and is based on different types of texts. The oral exercises concern more precisely French pronunciation. The course also includes practical training in written expression: the students are required to hand in a certain number of written papers and essays, which are analyzed and commented on by the lecturer. Above all, the course works on (1) formal letters and (2) literary and film critics. The course includes also a work on spelling by dictations and individual correction of homework.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Training of oral and written expression.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students: 1)  can interact with a degree of fluency and spontaneity in regular interaction with native speakers and take an active part in discussion in familiar contexts, accounting for and sustaining his views; 2) can describe experiences and events, narrate a story or relate the plot of a book or film and describe his reactions; 3) can present clear, detailed descriptions on a wide range of subjects and explain a viewpoint on a topical issue giving the advantages and disadvantages of various options; 4) can write clear, detailed text on a wide range of subjects which are familiar or of personal interest; 5) can write an essay or a report, passing on information or giving reasons in support of or against a particular point of view, and is able to write summaries and reviews of professional or literary works.
